    <h2 class="mt-5">System Access and Usage</h2>
    <p>
        Only authorized hospital personnel have access to this system. Access rights are granted based on the roles and responsibilities of the staff, and each user must authenticate their access credentials. Unauthorized individuals are strictly prohibited from accessing or attempting to access this system.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Data Collection and Usage</h2>
    <p>
        This Hospital Management System collects and manages patient information and related healthcare records. All collected data is intended solely for use in patient care, administrative purposes, and compliance with applicable laws. The hospital does not share any patient information outside the system without prior consent, except as required by law.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Data Security</h2>
    <p>
        The hospital has implemented stringent security measures to protect patient data and other sensitive information. The system is designed to prevent unauthorized access and to safeguard data integrity. Only authenticated users with the correct permissions can access patient information.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Restricted Use and Non-Disclosure</h2>
    <p>
        The use of this Hospital Management System is restricted to hospital personnel only. Users are required to keep their login credentials confidential and are strictly prohibited from disclosing any patient information to unauthorized individuals.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>
        The hospital reserves the right to modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Users will be notified of any significant changes. Continued use of the system constitutes acceptance of any updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2 class="mt-4">Contact Us</h2>
    <p>
        If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or the Hospital Management System, please contact the hospital's administration office.
    </p>
